$ /etc/sudoers

The *sudoers* file. It specifies who can run → Linux/shell/commands/sudo.

This file should be edited with → Linux/shell/commands/visudo.

Allow all → Linux/user[users] that are in the `sudo` → Linux/group to use sudo:
code {
%sudo ALL=(ALL) ALL
code }

Allow user named `fred` to use sudo:
code {
fred ALL=(ALL) ALL
code }
